00:15:41,221 --> 00:15:43,603
So you don't have to hire an illustrator to do all the art

351
00:15:43,623 --> 00:15:44,144
for your game.

352
00:15:44,464 --> 00:15:47,106
You just want to make the design really good when you

353
00:15:47,146 --> 00:15:48,107
send it to the publisher.

354
00:15:48,507 --> 00:15:50,389
And then they can layer the art on top of it.

355
00:15:52,991 --> 00:15:53,832
This is Skipity.

356
00:15:54,072 --> 00:15:54,793
It's a warning tail.

357
00:15:56,607 --> 00:16:02,673
So, when I submitted this to Mindware, I submitted it with plastic checker pieces and this beautiful

358
00:16:02,813 --> 00:16:04,555
wild board that's rainbow colored.

359
00:16:04,955 --> 00:16:07,277
And I like lots and lots of color in my designs.

360
00:16:07,778 --> 00:16:09,199
And so I made a really pretty board.

361
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:15,204
And it turns out, A, I think if I had submitted it with wooden pieces, I'd have wooden pieces.

362
00:16:16,085 --> 00:16:19,048
B, it's not a great board for game play.

363
00:16:19,887 --> 00:16:22,950
And the reason is people look at it and they get confused.

364
00:16:23,071 --> 00:16:25,373
They think that the colors on the board mean something,

365
00:16:25,473 --> 00:16:25,974
and they don't.

366
00:16:26,114 --> 00:16:27,295
They're just there to look pretty.

367
00:16:28,056 --> 00:16:29,658
So it intimidates people in a way

368
00:16:29,678 --> 00:16:31,420
that they don't need to be intimidated.

369
00:16:32,301 --> 00:16:33,863
And I submitted it to MindWare this way.

370
00:16:34,881 --> 00:16:38,826
And they tried a bunch of different designs and they didn't come up with anything they liked better.

371
00:16:38,866 --> 00:16:40,508
So they went back to my original design.

372
00:16:40,968 --> 00:16:44,673
So these are mistakes that I made on the prototype that came through on the final one.

373
00:16:44,993 --> 00:16:50,800
If I had it to do over again, I would do wooden checker pieces and I would do a calmer board that doesn't confuse people.

374
00:16:51,140 --> 00:16:54,404
And I may have it to do over again. We're considering reissuing it in a different format.

375
00:16:55,688 --> 00:16:58,052
Um, Color Stix.

376
00:16:59,034 --> 00:17:03,382
So Color Stix is a product that Mindware had for two years

377
00:17:03,462 --> 00:17:05,245
before they figured out how to manufacture it.

378
00:17:05,866 --> 00:17:06,788
I made it at home with.

379
00:17:08,115 --> 00:17:10,558
I cut the wooden sticks and I wrapped them with paper stickers.

380
00:17:10,998 --> 00:17:15,043
It's a game where you're lining the sticks up to make blocks of color.

381
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:18,807
And they had it for two years trying to figure out how they can manufacture it.

382
00:17:19,448 --> 00:17:23,452
And in the end, they found a manufacturer who would do the same thing I did in my prototype.

383
00:17:23,893 --> 00:17:26,135
They had wooden sticks with stickers wrapped around them.

384
00:17:26,916 --> 00:17:29,837
They tried a bunch of different things in between, but they came back to this.

385
00:17:29,957 --> 00:17:33,017
And I think part of it is that this is what they saw at the beginning and they knew how

386
00:17:33,078 --> 00:17:34,598
well it worked for the gameplay.

387
00:17:35,018 --> 00:17:38,839
So when they tried other forms, they didn't work as nice for the gameplay.

388
00:17:39,339 --> 00:17:42,120
They ended up having to cut the number of sticks in the game.

389
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:45,581
I think I originally had 60 and it went down to 42.

390
00:17:46,721 --> 00:17:51,522
And that was largely because that's what they had to do to get the nice quality of components.

391
00:17:52,582 --> 00:17:54,623
But it went back to the way that I had originally produced it.

392
00:17:56,224 --> 00:17:57,345
And this is Surplexed.

