00:18:24,052 --> 00:18:26,213
that were gonna line up the way we wanted them to

404
00:18:26,253 --> 00:18:26,853
for this game.

405
00:18:28,574 --> 00:18:30,495
Just the pre-made ones weren't working very well,

406
00:18:30,535 --> 00:18:32,015
cutting our own wasn't working at all.

407
00:18:32,516 --> 00:18:34,476
And so he decided to make a wooden prototype,

408
00:18:34,516 --> 00:18:36,377
and I said, well, they're not gonna make it out of wood,

409
00:18:36,417 --> 00:18:37,158
but sure, that works.

410
00:18:37,878 --> 00:18:40,020
And so we took it to Toy Fair and we showed it to Mindware.

411
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:42,202
They loved it, they took the game the way it was,

412
00:18:42,282 --> 00:18:43,563
and they produced it in wood.

413
00:18:44,124 --> 00:18:45,865
And if I'd shown them a chipboard prototype,

414
00:18:45,925 --> 00:18:47,667
I wouldn't have gotten a final wooden one.

415
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:50,009
So it's just, I think it's really important

416
00:18:50,069 --> 00:18:52,171
that when you show your game to the publishers,

417
00:18:52,331 --> 00:18:54,293
it's as close as it can possibly be

418
00:18:54,693 --> 00:18:55,514
to what you want it to be.

